'''Keurboomstrand''' is a [[resort town]] near [[Plettenberg Bay]] on the [[Western Cape]] of [[South Africa]]. It takes its name from the [[Indigenous (ecology)|indigenous]] [[Virgilia (plant)|keurboom]] tree which grows in the region. The [[Keurbooms River]] runs nearby.
